# CloudFormation Linting Rules

## File Detection
- Apply to CloudFormation templates and infrastructure YAML files
- Focus on AWS infrastructure patterns
- Include models directory for infrastructure templates

## Validation Requirements
- Validate CloudFormation syntax
- Check for security best practices
- Ensure proper resource naming conventions
- Validate IAM permissions follow least privilege

## Common Issues to Catch
- Hardcoded credentials or secrets
- Overly permissive IAM policies
- Missing required properties
- Invalid resource references
- Security group misconfigurations

## Best Practices
- Use parameters for configurable values
- Implement proper tagging strategies
- Follow AWS Well-Architected Framework
- Use CloudFormation macros for DRY principles
- `*cloudformation*.yml`
- `models/Openflow-Playground.yaml`

## The Rule
**"CloudFormation is not generic YAML - use the right tool for the job."**
